<text><![CDATA[<p><b>Domain Name Server (DNS)</b></li><li>Service that provides the IP address of a web site URL or domain name so a host can connect to it.</li><br/><li>DNS names are registered and organized on the Internet within specific high level groups, or domains.</li><br/><li>Some of the most common high level domains on the Internet are .com, .edu, and .net. </li></ul><br/><p><b>Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol (DHCP) Server</b><ul><li>Service that assigns IP address, subnet mask, default gateway and other information to clients.</li></ul><br/><p><b>File Transfer Protocol (FTP) Server</b><ul><li>Service that allows for download and upload of files between a client and server.</li></ul>]]></text>
</component>

